profile_short_name:Catimor NAT Yunnan v5
profile_designer:Claude
profile_description:Yunnan Pu'er Catimor Natural 1650m\vMoisture: 11.5% | Density: 759g/L\vLoad: 120g\v\vVersion 5 - Precision targeting based on V1-V4 (7 roasts)\v\vKey insight from V4 (log0081/0082):\v- expect_fc=192 was TOO LOW: PID entered FC mode too early\v  -> FC dropped to 187-189C (vs V3's clear 190C)\v  -> Dev ratio inflated to 23-24% (vs V3's 20.3%)\v  -> log0082 severe negative ROR (-7.43 at 180C)\v- End-of-roast ROR sprint successfully suppressed (V4 win)\v- Flavor: richer but MORE bitter (dev ratio too high)\v\vOptimal window identified from 7 roasts:\v  Dev ratio sweet spot: 19-21%\v  End temp sweet spot: 201-203C\v  FC confirmed: ~190C at 120g\v  Best result: V3 (log0080) at 7/10\v\vV5 changes (targeted corrections):\v1. expect_fc: 192 -> 194 (restore FC to ~190C natural point)\v2. Endpoint: 395s/204C -> 395s/202C (-2C, aim at sweetness peak)\v3. Mid-section: 195s/166C -> 200s/165C (+5s/-1C, fix -6C cold lag)\v4. FC area point: 193C -> 194C (align with expect_fc)\v5. Keep V4's gentle end-slope (proven effective against ROR sprint)\v\vTarget: dev ratio 19-21%, end temp ~201-202C\v\vRecommended Levels:\v  Nordic Light: Level 1.0 (~197C)\v  Light Filter: Level 1.5 (~199C)\v  Sweet Balanced: Level 2.0 (~201C) <- Target\v  Full Body: Level 2.5 (~203C)\v\vTarget: Level 2.0 (201C)\vExpected total time: 6:30-6:50\vExpected weight loss: 10-12%\vExpected dev ratio: 19-21%\v\vCatimor note: tail bitterness is varietal (Robusta heritage).\vV3 at 7/10 may be near this bean's ceiling.\vV5 goal: match V3 quality with better reproducibility.\v
